      <div class="char-section">
        <h3 class="t-en">Notable Moments</h3>
        <h3 class="t-id">Momen Penting</h3>
        <p class="t-en">
          <em>The Negotiation. Session II.</em> Preparing to talk the windmill goblins into
          neutrality, Nanang cast several spells to enhance his charisma and opened a conversation.
          The goblins attacked. The reason was not obscure: Sogong and Anaik had been moving
          through the rear in full plate. Nanang's response to the wasted spell slots was not
          measured. Sogong offered context.
        </p>
        <p class="t-en" style="margin-top:0.8rem;">
          <em>Sorry for Being Arrogant. Session II.</em> Watching Anaik charge uphill during
          the gnoll fight, Nanang said: "Finally I'm not being targeted and I won't be." Both
          gnoll hunters on the hill immediately shot at him, despite having Anaik and Sogong
          standing directly between them. Six arrows; he avoided five. He yelled "Sorry for
          being arrogant" while in the process of avoiding them. The chronicle records this as
          possibly the fastest acknowledgment of consequence this group has produced.
        </p>
        <p class="t-en" style="margin-top:0.8rem;">
          <em>"Think Kids, Think." Session II.</em> Having produced a crow in response to
          Traxex's request for fog, and then a cat illusion, Nanang stood by as the Warlord
          attacked both rather than Traxex, who was available on the high ground directly
          beside them. Then: "Think kids, think. Had I casted the fog, you wouldn't be able
          to attack." Traxex had no rebuttal. The chronicle records this as the moment Nanang
          was most completely correct, and the most difficult moment in the chronicle's history
          to record without editorial comment.
        </p>
        <p class="t-id">
          <em>Negosiasi. Sesi II.</em> Bersiap membujuk goblin-goblin kincir angin agar netral, Nanang gunakan beberapa mantra untuk meningkatkan pesonanya dan memulai percakapan. Para goblin menyerang. Alasannya tidak tersembunyi: Sogong dan Anaik sudah bergerak dari belakang dengan pelat penuh. Respons Nanang terhadap slot mantra yang terbuang tidak terukur. Sogong memberikan konteks.
        </p>
        <p class="t-id" style="margin-top:0.8rem;">
          <em>Maaf Sudah Sombong. Sesi II.</em> Menyaksikan Anaik menerobos menanjak selama pertempuran gnoll, Nanang berkata: "Akhirnya aku tidak jadi target dan tidak akan jadi." Kedua pemburu gnoll di bukit itu langsung menembaknya, meskipun ada Anaik dan Sogong berdiri tepat di antara mereka. Enam anak panah; ia hindari lima. Ia berteriak "Maaf sudah sombong" sambil menghindarinya. Kronik mencatat ini sebagai mungkin pengakuan konsekuensi tercepat yang pernah dihasilkan kelompok ini.
        </p>
        <p class="t-id" style="margin-top:0.8rem;">
          <em>"Think Kids, Think." Sesi II.</em> Setelah menghasilkan seekor gagak sebagai respons atas permintaan Traxex untuk kabut, lalu ilusi kucing, Nanang menonton saat Warlord menyerang keduanya daripada Traxex yang tersedia di tanah tinggi tepat di sampingnya. Lalu: "Think kids, think. Kalau aku gunakan kabut, kalian tidak akan bisa menyerang." Traxex tidak punya sanggahan. Kronik mencatat ini sebagai momen Nanang paling sepenuhnya benar, dan momen paling sulit dalam sejarah kronik untuk dicatat tanpa komentar editorial.
        </p>
      </div>

